                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/1235: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-08-02T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 2, 1930—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 3—11:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>653. With reference to telegrams from the American Consul at Hankow transmitted
                    to the Commander in Chief, the latter has replied as follows July 31st: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“There are now 3 American gunboats in the vicinity of Hankow. The U.S.
                            Steamship <hi rend="italic">Luzon</hi> is leaving Changsha, August 1st.
                            In my opinion there is appropriate naval protection for Hankow and the
                            difference [<hi rend="italic">difficulty?</hi>] is due to the failure of
                            nationals to seek a place of safety and remain away from unsafe places
                            after repeated instructions from the Legation and consular authorities
                            to do so. There are also reported 10 foreign men-of-war in the vicinity
                            of Hankow and vessels of all navies are acting in concert.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
